---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Advertising Terms & Conditions" description="Terms and conditions for advertising with Future Media.">
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Advertising T&amp;Cs</h1>
      <p>Terms and conditions governing advertising placements with Future Media.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="container page-content__inner">
      <h2>1. General Terms</h2>
      <p>All advertising placements with Future Media are subject to these terms and conditions. By placing an advertisement, the advertiser agrees to be bound by these terms.</p>

      <h2>2. Booking & Payment</h2>
      <p>All bookings must be confirmed in writing. Payment terms are net 30 days from invoice date unless otherwise agreed. Future Media reserves the right to withhold advertising until payment is received.</p>

      <h2>3. Creative Standards</h2>
      <p>All advertising creative must comply with the Advertising Standards Authority of Namibia (ASAN) code of practice. Future Media reserves the right to reject any creative that does not meet our standards or applicable regulations.</p>

      <h2>4. Cancellation Policy</h2>
      <p>Cancellations must be submitted in writing. Cancellations received more than 14 days before the campaign start date will receive a full refund. Cancellations within 14 days are subject to a 50% cancellation fee.</p>

      <h2>5. Liability</h2>
      <p>Future Media shall not be liable for any failure to broadcast or display advertisements due to circumstances beyond our reasonable control, including technical failures, force majeure, or regulatory action.</p>

      <h2>6. Rate Changes</h2>
      <p>Published rate cards are valid for the period stated. Future Media reserves the right to adjust rates with 30 days written notice to existing clients.</p>

      <p>For questions about these terms, contact <a href="mailto:legal@futuremedia.com.na" style="color: #E3564E;">legal@futuremedia.com.na</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
